FeedPackage.Authors: Jeffrey Stedfast, Atsushi Enomoto, and Mono contributors
FeedPackage.Description:
The main goal of this project is to supply a portable alternative to System.Text.Encoding that can be used from other PCL libraries.
Platforms such as Silverlight and Windows Phone currently do not provide support for text encodings other than a limited subset of the Unicode encodings. This can be a real show-stopper when you need to work with legacy text encodings.
Currently supported encodings include: ASCII, Latin1, and all Unicode encodings (including UTF-7 and UTF-8).
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: * Initial release.
FeedPackage.Summary: A Portable Implementation of System.Text.Encoding.
FeedPackage.Tags: silverlight winrt wp8
FeedPackage.Title: Portable.Text.Encoding

FeedPackage.Authors: Jeffrey Stedfast, Atsushi Enomoto, and Mono contributors
FeedPackage.Description:
The main goal of this project is to supply a portable alternative to System.Text.Encoding that can be used from other PCL libraries.
Platforms such as Windows Phone currently do not provide support for text encodings other than a limited subset of the Unicode encodings. This can be a real show-stopper when you need to work with legacy text encodings.

FeedPackage.Description: Portable IOC is a tiny (less than 200 lines of code) thread-safe and portable Inversion of Control container. It is designed to make it simple and easy to wire dependencies for client projects include various versions of the Windows Phone, the new Windows 8 Store apps, Silverlight, and will support the desktop as well. Features include dependency resolution, lifetime management, constructor and property injection, control over registration and multiple instance support.

FeedPackage.Description: Light-weight, portable logging interface. Combine with PortableLog adapters for logging frameworks or write your own.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes:
Simplify the API and implementation.
Removed -Format method overloads, after some use it seemed better to use string.Format() explicitly or string extension methods like format.With(args). This removed the need for ILogEx to resolve the overload ambiguities and simplified the API overall.
Breaking changes: * Remove ILogEx * Remove -Ex log method overloads * Remove -Format log method overloads * Rename some types to simpler names, such as ILogExFactory to ILogFactory * Change log method signatures to resolve ambiguity in overloads

FeedPackage.Description: A lightweight implementation of ASP.NET MVC APIs for mobile devices.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: Initial release.
FeedPackage.Summary: PortableRazor is a mobile framework that provides a lightweight implementation of ASP.NET MVC APIs along with a simple route handler. Combined, these features encapsulate the construction of hybrid-friendly URLs inside of a webview, and provide the hooks to intercept these URLs in order to call .NET code.

FeedPackage.Description: A template to simplify integration of the PortableRazor Plugin for Xamarin and Windows in your app.
FeedPackage.ReleaseNotes: First release of PortableRazor Starter Pack
FeedPackage.Summary:
PortableRazor makes it easy to create hybrid mobile apps in C# using the Razor templating engine, and ASP.NET MVC-style APIs and routing.
PortableRazor StarterPack simplifies the integration of PortableRazor into cross-platform apps that share code through PCLs, providing cross-platform management of static resources, like CSS, Javascript, images and database files.
This NuGet references these plugins: * PortableRazor - lightweight implementation of ASP.NET MVC APIs for mobile devices * PCLStorage - a portable set of local file IO APIs for .NET * EmbeddedResource Plugin for Xamarin and Windows - cross-platform access to embedded resources
When installed in an iOS, Android, or Windows Phone project, a source implementation of PortableRazor.IHybridWebView.cs is added to the project.
When referenced from a PCL project, a source Starter.cs implementation is added to the project, along with an example Model, View, and Controller.
FeedPackage.Tags: xamarin pcl xam.pcl windows phone winphone wp8 winrt android xamarin.forms ios
FeedPackage.Title: PortableRazor.StarterPack
